      "name": "Benchmark hemolysis index validation against FDA experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against FDA centrifugal pump experimental measurements at five operating points. RH < 1 at all points. The validation campaign included a 128-run LHS UQ sweep with Sobol sensitivity indices computed for impeller clearance, rotational speed, and blood viscosity; full UQ results are tabulated in Appendix C of the validation report. All predicted NIH values fell within experimental uncertainty bands."
