    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scope. RH < 1 at all five operating points confirms the CFD model conservatively predicts hemolysis relative to the predicate device benchmark. The UQ campaign (128-run LHS, Sobol indices) documented in the validation report confirms that model predictions are robust to input variability within the COU envelope. The credibility evidence package is sufficient to support the regulatory decision for the Class II CPB device at Medium assurance level.",
